author: Agencies Manila The
title: 2 Australian landing ships for Philippines
text:
Agencies
Manila
The Philippine Navy will be commissioning into service two ships to be donated by Australia next week.
The two landing craft heavy ships are a gift from the Australian government to the Philippines and will be turned over to the Philippine Navy on July 23. Flag officer in command, Vice Admiral Jesus Millan said the ships have been scheduled to arrive in the country by first week of August.
Millan said the commissioning would be done in Australia while the christening of the two ships would be done in the Philippines.
